   460→
   461→## Integrate the <GlareHover /> component from React Bits
   462→
   463→You are helping integrate an open-source React component into an existing application.
   464→
   465→### Component: GlareHover
   466→### Variant: JavaScript + CSS
   467→
   468→
   469→---
   470→
   471→### Usage Example
   472→```jsx
   473→import GlareHover from './GlareHover'
   474→
   475→<div style={{ height: '600px', position: 'relative' }}>
   476→  <GlareHover
   477→    glareColor="#ffffff"
   478→    glareOpacity={0.3}
   479→    glareAngle={-30}
   480→    glareSize={300}
   481→    transitionDuration={800}
   482→    playOnce={false}
   483→  >
   484→    <h2 style={{ fontSize: '3rem', fontWeight: '900', color: '#333', margin: 0 }}>
   485→      Hover Me
   486→    </h2>
   487→  </GlareHover>
   488→</div>
   489→```
   490→
   491→### Props
   492→| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
   493→|------|------|---------|-------------|
   494→| width | string | 500px | The width of the hover element. |
   495→| height | string | 500px | The height of the hover element. |
   496→| background | string | #000 | The background color of the element. |
   497→| borderRadius | string | 10px | The border radius of the element. |
   498→| borderColor | string | #333 | The border color of the element. |
   499→| children | React.ReactNode | undefined | The content to display inside the glare hover element. |
   500→| glareColor | string | #ffffff | The color of the glare effect (hex format). |
   501→| glareOpacity | number | 0.5 | The opacity of the glare effect (0-1). |
   502→| glareAngle | number | -45 | The angle of the glare effect in degrees. |
   503→| glareSize | number | 250 | The size of the glare effect as a percentage (e.g. 250 = 250%). |
